[Surging](https://github.com/dotnetcore/surging)  Is a service engine framework based on dotnetcore. It has a problem for a long time. Can you help me? Because need to make the business module hot update, need to generate a dynamic proxy at runtime to achieve grayscale publishing, but use AssemblyLoadContext hot The update loader throws an exception `AssemblyLoadContext is unloading or was already unloaded.`, the code  follows:
```c#
        var stream = CompilationUtilitys.CompileClientProxy(trees,
                assemblys
                    .Select(a => MetadataReference.CreateFromFile(a.Location))
                    .Concat(new[]
                    {
                        MetadataReference.CreateFromFile(typeof(Task).GetTypeInfo().Assembly.Location)
                    }),
                _logger);

            using (stream)
            {
#if NET
                var assembly = Assembly.Load(stream.ToArray());
#else
                var assembly = AssemblyLoadContext.Default.LoadFromStream(stream);
#endif
               return assembly.GetExportedTypes();
}
```

After checking the [AssemblyLoadContext](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/blob/2c61b985c0513d9a70eee7221fa15910e7003d16/src/System.Private.CoreLib/shared/System/Runtime/Loader/AssemblyLoadContext.cs), when calling LoadFromStream, first call VerifyIsAlive to check, and when the AssemblyLoadContext is destructed, it will set _state to InternalState.Unloading, which causes the AssemblyLoadContext.Default.LoadFromStream to throw an AssemblyLoadContext_Verify_NotUnloading exception. Can you help me solve it? ?
